definition: down/downwards/below/lower/later/next (week etc)/second (of two parts)/to decline/to go down/to arrive at (a decision, conclusion etc)/measure word to show the frequency of an action

sentences.english: Oh no! I mean fuscous jacket I'm wearing, Your Royal Highness.

sentences.chinese: 陛下，這個人無處不在，要找到他，太難了。

sentences.english: As a sire, he certainly changed greyhound racing.
sentences.chinese: 作爲一個陛下，他肯定有改變賽狗。

sentences.english: We were unaware that you had a Brother, Lord Protector.
sentences.chinese: 我們不知道你還有一個兄弟啊，護國公陛下。

sentences.english: It is His Majesty for your special items, small people can not wear.

sentences.english: Yes, Her Majesty hovered over the proceedings, an unseen meta-judge.

sentences.english: If it please Your Grace, we want no part of him.

sentences.english: Their Majesties will open the new bridge today.

sentences.chinese: 尊敬的陛下，您當然比我知道得清楚。
